, {"label": 1, "content": "It is generally safe to use topical corticosteroids, such as prednisone, for the treatment of impetigo in children. Corticosteroids can help to reduce inflammation and redness in the affected area, and may also help to speed up the healing process. However, it is important to use these medications as directed by a healthcare professional and to follow their recommendations for use.\n\nIt is possible that the oral antibiotic prescribed to your daughter was not effective at eliminating the bacteria causing the impetigo, which is why the lesions continued to appear. In such cases, a different antibiotic may be needed. Alternatively, the prednisone ointment may help to reduce the inflammation and improve the appearance of the lesions, even if the bacteria are not completely eliminated.\n\nIt is important to continue using the ointment as directed and to follow up with your healthcare provider if you have any concerns about your daughter's treatment. It is also important to practice good hygiene, such as washing your hands frequently and keeping the affected area clean, to help prevent the spread of infection."}, {"label": 0, "content": "hi sir, welcome to HCG, i understand ur problem clearly, tusq d lozanges also there, use that u will get better results, hope u satisfy with my answer, thank u.. have a nice day..."}, {"label": 1, "content": "There are several over-the-counter (OTC) medications that contain dextromethorphan, a cough suppressant, that may be effective in relieving cough associated with a cold. Some examples include:\n\nRobitussin DM: This product contains dextromethorphan and guaifenesin, an expectorant that helps to thin and loosen mucus in the airways.\n\nVicks DayQuil Cough: This product contains dextromethorphan, guaifenesin, and acetaminophen, a pain reliever.\n\nNyQuil Cough: This product contains dextromethorphan, doxylamine succinate (a sedating antihistamine), and acetaminophen.\n\nDelsym: This product is a liquid form of dextromethorphan that can be taken orally or added to water and used as a throat spray.\n\nIt's important to follow the dosing instructions on the packaging and not exceed the recommended dose. Dextromethorphan can cause drowsiness, so it's important not to drive or operate heavy machinery while taking it. If you have any concerns about taking these medications or if your cough persists despite treatment, it's always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional."}, {"label": 0, "content": "stress fractures at lower end of tibia is very common at your age.They are caused by trivial traumas,so unnoticeable injury usually.please undergo MRI of affected ankle joint."}, {"label": 1, "content": "There are many possible causes of pain and swelling near the ankle, and it is not possible to determine the exact cause without a physical examination and additional information. Some possible causes of pain and swelling in the ankle include:\n\nSprained ankle: This is a common injury that occurs when the ligaments in the ankle are stretched or torn. It can cause pain, swelling, and difficulty walking.\n\nFracture: A fracture is a break in a bone. If the ankle is fractured, it can cause pain, swelling, and difficulty walking.\n\nTendinitis: Tendinitis is inflammation of a tendon, which is a cord of tissue that connects muscle to bone. Tendinitis in the ankle can cause pain and swelling.\n\nGout: Gout is a type of arthritis that is caused by the accumulation of uric acid crystals in the joints. It can cause sudden, severe pain, swelling, and redness in the affected joint.\n\nInfection: An infection in the ankle can cause pain, swelling, and redness.\n\nPoor circulation: Poor circulation in the legs can cause swelling and pain in the ankles.\n\nIt is important to see a doctor to determine the cause of the pain and swelling in your ankle. The doctor will ask about your medical history, perform a physical examination, and possibly order additional tests to diagnose the problem. Treatment will depend on the underlying cause."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hi ThereIf you are a physically active person then a rate of 50bpm is ok, yes its quite likely to have breathing problems due to inhalation of chemicals at work place. I would like to suggest you to take proper precautions like using certified masks at work place. And also get a CHEST XRAY PA View done to rule out any lung pathology.Good Luck"}, {"label": 1, "content": "It's important to talk to a healthcare provider about your symptoms. Low heart rate (bradycardia) and dizziness can be caused by a variety of factors, including medications, underlying medical conditions, and lifestyle factors. A healthcare provider can help determine the cause of your symptoms and recommend appropriate treatment.\n\nIt's also important to mention your history of shortness of breath and potential exposure to cleaning chemicals at your workplace. These symptoms could be related to an underlying medical condition or the chemicals you were exposed to.\n\nIn the meantime, it's a good idea to try to get plenty of rest, stay hydrated, and avoid activities that may exacerbate your symptoms. If you experience any severe or persistent symptoms, such as fainting, chest pain, or difficulty breathing, seek medical attention immediately."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hello!Thank you for posting here.This discomfort is not because of the bone graft.Take a sterile gauze piece and wet it.Keep the wet gauze in the area of the suture. Change the gauze piece from time to time and after every meal.Gargle after every meal and snack.Your doctor will remove the excess suture material.See him as early as possible as you do not want the suture material to get infected.Apply a soothing quadragel like ointment in the area if ulceration appears.Hope this helps."}, {"label": 1, "content": "I'm sorry to hear about the discomfort you're experiencing following your bone graft. Here are a few suggestions for how you can try to alleviate your discomfort:\n\nOver-the-counter pain medication: You can try taking over-the-counter pain medication, such as acetaminophen (Tylenol) or ibuprofen (Advil), to help reduce discomfort and inflammation. Be sure to follow the instructions on the label and speak with your dentist or physician before taking any new medications.\n\nCold compresses: Applying a cold compress to the affected area can help numb the pain and reduce swelling. You can make a cold compress by wrapping a bag of ice or a bag of frozen vegetables in a towel and applying it to the area for about 20 minutes at a time.\n\nSaltwater rinse: Rinsing your mouth with saltwater can help reduce swelling and kill bacteria, which can help with discomfort. To make a saltwater rinse, mix 1/2 teaspoon of salt with 8 ounces of warm water. Rinse your mouth with the solution, being sure to rinse the affected area thoroughly.\n\nAvoid hard or crunchy foods: It's important to be gentle with your grafted area while it heals. Avoid eating hard or crunchy foods that may cause additional discomfort or damage to the area. Stick to soft, easy-to-chew foods until you are able to eat more normally.\n\nIf your discomfort persists or becomes worse, be sure to contact your dentist or physician. They will be able to assess your condition and provide additional guidance on how to manage your discomfort."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hello Welcome to health care magic I can understand your situation. I appreciate your effort to seek online support. As per your details, he is possibly having underlying anxiety/depression. For this consult a psychiatrist for detailed evaluation. Following treatment strategies would be helpful- 1) Antidepressants/Antianxiety agents like SSRIs (escitalopram, sertarline, paroxetine etc) 2) Antianxiety agents like clonazepam, lorazepam, alprazolam etc3) Psychotherapy/ Counselling sessions4) Relaxation techniques like yoga, meditation, deep breathing etc Hope it helps Good luck Regards Dr. Gourav Monga Consultant Psychiatrist"}, {"label": 1, "content": "It is possible that your son is experiencing depression and that his physical symptoms may be related. Depression can cause a lack of energy and appetite, as well as difficulty sleeping. It is also possible that the injury and time off of sports has contributed to his feelings of sadness and loss of motivation. It is important to seek medical attention for your son to determine the cause of his symptoms and to determine the best course of treatment.\n\nI would recommend scheduling an appointment with your son's primary care doctor or a mental health professional. They will be able to assess your son's physical and emotional health and provide recommendations for treatment. It may also be helpful for your son to participate in activities that he enjoys and to try to maintain a healthy lifestyle by eating nutritious meals and getting regular exercise. Encouraging your son to talk about his feelings and concerns can also be beneficial.\n\nIt is important to take care of your son's physical and emotional health. If you are concerned about his well-being, it is important to seek help as soon as possible."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hello,Folvite is a vitamin supplement useful as a prenatal vitamin to help facilitate conception and to prevent neural tube defects after conception. It is routinely given along with other B-complex medication when one is trying to conceive. The methyl-tetrahydrofolate form is safe and useful even in pregnancy. Yet, since you have been trying to conceive for the past one year, you should get all the protocol investigations done and management planned accordingly. Hope this helps."}, {"label": 1, "content": "Folivite is a brand of folic acid, a B vitamin that is important for proper fetal development. It is often recommended for women who are trying to get pregnant or who are in the early stages of pregnancy to help prevent birth defects of the brain and spine. Folic acid can be found in certain foods, such as leafy green vegetables, beans, and fortified grains, but it is also available in supplement form.\n\nTaking folic acid before and during pregnancy can help reduce the risk of certain birth defects. It is especially important to get enough folic acid in the early weeks of pregnancy, before many women even know they are pregnant. It is generally recommended that women who are planning to get pregnant take a daily folic acid supplement of at least 400 micrograms (mcg) before and during pregnancy.\n\nIf your wife has been advised to take Folivite by her doctor, it is important that she follow the doctor's instructions and take the medication as directed. It is also important for your wife to discuss any concerns or questions she may have about the medication with her doctor."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Thanks for your question on Health Care Magic. I can understand your concern. No, this is not common. Foul smelling discharge in rectal cancer patient suggest infection at tumour site. Chemotherapy makes patient immunocompromised. So chances of infection are high in these patients. Radiotherapy weakens local defense system. So both these make patient prone to infection. So better to get done culture and sensitivity report of discharge. Culture report will isolate the causative organism and sensitivity report will guide you better about effective antibiotic treatment. He needs antibiotics.Hope I have solved your query. Wishing good health to your father. Thanks."}, {"label": 1, "content": "A milky white discharge with a foul smell can be caused by an infection or inflammation in the reproductive or urinary system. In men, this can occur in the prostate gland or urethra. In your father's case, the discharge and foul smell could potentially be related to the rectal cancer or its treatment. It is important for your father to speak with his healthcare provider about this symptom, as it could be a sign of an infection or other complication that needs medical attention. The healthcare provider will be able to examine your father and recommend the appropriate treatment."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Here you have told about symptoms like back pain and shock like pain or sensatiin in inner hip as well the back of the foot. This kind of pain is usually related to back pain(spinal issue related with disc and nerve) only and rarely it may also be related to vitamin B deficiency along with less water intake.I suggest to visit a orthopedic and get your self examine properly, if needed go for x ray and then do take blood report to know about vitamin B level in body. As per the report and evaluation doctor will suggest for the precautionary treatment with medication. I suggest also visit a physio for postural correction, advice on back and leg strengthening and stretching exercises. And also do follow it.You can also use a hot bag at your back for some relief in pain.As per your symptoms what you have given nothing looks major so I have given you simple guideline and I am sure you will feel better once you start taking steps on it. Take care."}, {"label": 1, "content": "There are several potential causes of electric shock-like pain in the inner hip or groin area. Some possibilities include:\n\nMusculoskeletal problems: Pain in the inner hip or groin area can be caused by muscle strains or sprains, or by problems with the bones or joints in the area. This type of pain may be accompanied by other symptoms such as swelling, bruising, or difficulty moving the affected area.\n\nNerve problems: Pain in the inner hip or groin area can also be caused by irritation or compression of a nerve in the area. This type of pain may be accompanied by numbness, tingling, or weakness in the affected area.\n\nVascular problems: Pain in the inner hip or groin area can also be caused by problems with the blood vessels in the area. This type of pain may be accompanied by other symptoms such as changes in skin color, temperature, or sensation.\n\nIt is important to see a healthcare provider for an evaluation and proper diagnosis if you are experiencing electric shock-like pain in the inner hip or groin area, or if you have any other symptoms that concern you. The provider will be able to determine the cause of your pain and recommend appropriate treatment."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hello and welcome to HCM.As an Urologist,i can understand your concern.Protein needs to be restricted only in kidney failure patients.Whether your pain is kidney related,can be confirmed by doing a scan.An ultrasound scan-KUB,will show clearly,if there's any kidney injury.To clear doubts, get examined by an Urologist, with following reports.urine and blood routine,and creatinine. These reports will clear all doubts .If you've any doubts,send the reports to me, as a direct question.Dr.Matthew J. Mangat."}, {"label": 1, "content": "It's important to pay attention to any changes in your body, including the symptoms you are experiencing. Mild pain in the right kidney area could potentially be caused by a variety of factors, such as a urinary tract infection, kidney stones, or even just muscle strain if you have been exercising more intensely recently. The salty flavor in your mouth and lips could be related to the increased protein intake and increased urination, as the kidneys help to filter excess fluids and electrolytes from the body.\n\nIt's always a good idea to speak with a healthcare professional if you are experiencing any concerning symptoms or if the pain persists. They can help to determine the cause of the pain and provide appropriate treatment. In the meantime, it may be helpful to drink plenty of fluids, including water, to help flush any potential irritants out of your urinary tract and to relieve any discomfort. You should also try to reduce your intake of salty foods and drinks, as these can exacerbate the symptoms you are experiencing."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hello and Welcome to \u2018Ask A Doctor\u2019 service.I have reviewed your query and here is my advice. It looks like a fungal infection like seborrhea.Apply topical anti fungal ointments like Clotrimazole for symptomatic relief. Keep the area clean and dry.In case of secondary infection, start a short course of antibiotics for five to seven days. Clotrimazole-Neosporins combination is a better choice. Hope I have answered your query.Let me know if I can assist you further."}, {"label": 1, "content": "There are several possible causes of an itchy rash in the armpit, including irritation or allergy to certain substances, infections, or other underlying medical conditions. Without more information, it is difficult to give specific treatment recommendations. Here are some general steps you can take to help manage an itchy rash in the armpit:\n\nKeep the affected area clean and dry. Avoid using harsh soaps or detergents on the skin, as these can be irritating.\n\nApply a cool compress to the affected area to help reduce itching and inflammation.\n\nAvoid activities that may cause sweating in the affected area.\n\nAvoid scratching the affected area, as this can make the rash worse and lead to infection.\n\nUse over-the-counter (OTC) creams or ointments, such as hydrocortisone cream, to help reduce itching and inflammation.\n\nIf the rash does not improve within a few days, or if you have other symptoms such as fever or lymph node swelling, you should see a healthcare provider for further evaluation and treatment. A healthcare provider may prescribe stronger medications, such as oral steroids or antibiotics, if necessary.\n\nIt is important to identify and address the underlying cause of the rash, as this will help to prevent recurrence."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hello,Sorry to hear that you were bitten by a dog.  It is reassuring knowing you were bitten by your own dog as opposed to a feral dog because wild dogs carry much more bacteria and even rabies.  The use of antibiotics for prophylactics is controversial.  The first-line oral therapy is amoxicillin-clavulanate. For higher-risk infections, a first dose of antibiotic may be given intravenously.  Bactrim is a medicine that is used in various animal bites but it is not the first choice based on the types of bacteria generally contained in dog bites.  However, if you are to use it, you need to get a full dosage and not just whatever is left over from a previous infection."}, {"label": 1, "content": "It's important to properly clean and treat a dog bite as soon as possible to prevent infection. Here's what you can do:\n\nWash the wound thoroughly with soap and water. Do this for at least 5 minutes to help remove any bacteria from the wound.\n\nApply a disinfectant to the wound. You can use rubbing alcohol, hydrogen peroxide, or iodine.\n\nCover the wound with a sterile bandage. This will help keep it clean and protected.\n\nKeep the wound elevated. This will help reduce swelling.\n\nTake over-the-counter pain medication as needed. Ibuprofen or acetaminophen can help reduce pain and inflammation.\n\nWatch for signs of infection, such as increased pain, redness, swelling, or drainage from the wound. If you notice any of these signs, you should contact a healthcare provider as soon as possible.\n\nAs for taking Bactrim DS for the infection, it's important to consult with a healthcare provider before taking any medication. Bactrim DS is a prescription antibiotic that is used to treat a variety of bacterial infections, but it may not be the most appropriate treatment for a skin infection. It's always best to consult with a healthcare provider to determine the most appropriate treatment for your specific situation. They can assess the severity of the infection and recommend the most effective treatment."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hi, dear. I have gone through your question. I can understand your concern. You have anemia but from this report only we can not say its always due to iron deficiency. Thete are many othet causes. Even vitamin B12 deficiency may produce same. Sp you should go for peripherals smear examination and serum iron and ferritine level.  If ypur iron and ferritine level comes low tjen you should take iron treatment.  Otherwise tale treatment according to cause.Hope I have answered your question, if you have doubt then I will be happy to answer. Thanks for using health care magic. Wish you a very good health."}, {"label": 1, "content": "Iron supplements are typically recommended when a person has low levels of iron in their body, which can lead to iron-deficiency anemia. There are several ways to determine if you have low iron levels, including a blood test to measure your iron levels and other indicators of anemia, such as the amount of hemoglobin in your red blood cells.\n\nThe results of your blood test suggest that you may not have low iron levels. Your hemoglobin and hematocrit levels are within the normal range, which suggests that you have sufficient iron in your body. However, it is important to note that these tests can sometimes be affected by other factors, such as inflammation or certain medications, so it is always best to consult with a healthcare provider for a proper diagnosis.\n\nIf you are concerned about your iron levels or the recommendation for iron supplements, I recommend discussing your concerns with your healthcare provider. They can help you understand the results of your blood test and determine the best course of action for your specific situation."}, {"label": 0, "content": "YOU ARE NOT ASTHMATICYOUR SYMPTOMPS ARE OF ALLERGIESWHEN YOU EXERCISE YOUR DEMAND FOR OXYGEN INCREASES AND THERE IS DIFFICULITYYOU GET YOUR BLOOD SERUM TESTED FOR SPECIFIC ANTIBODIES OF COMMON FOODSTILL THENYOU TAKE ALLEGRA 120 MGM DAILYSUP TOSSEX 1/2 TSF AT NIGHTTAB RHINITIDINE 150 MGM IN MORNINGPOST AFTER RESULTS"}, {"label": 1, "content": "It is possible that you have exercise-induced asthma, which is a form of asthma that is triggered by physical activity. People with exercise-induced asthma may have difficulty breathing during or after exercise, but may not experience any symptoms at other times. In some cases, people with exercise-induced asthma may only have symptoms when they exercise in cold or dry air.\n\nIf your doctor has diagnosed you with asthma, it is important to follow their treatment recommendations and use any prescribed medications as directed. It is also a good idea to try to avoid exercising in cold or dry air, as this can trigger symptoms. If you are having difficulty breathing while sitting down and are not engaging in physical activity, it is important to discuss this with your doctor to determine the cause and appropriate treatment."}, {"label": 0, "content": "HiThanks for using healthcare magicI think, you have impulse disorder and in that case, you need help of a psychiatrist to control it. You need low dose antidepressant and benzodiazepine that would help to control these symptoms. These drugs are not available over the counter and you need prescription for them. Better to take help of a psychiatrist for proper diagnosis and management. In case, you need further help, you can ask.Thanka"}, {"label": 1, "content": "Eating a lot of ice, a condition known as \"pagophagia,\" can be harmful to your health in a number of ways.\n\nFirst, it can damage your teeth. Chewing on hard objects, such as ice, can cause tooth fractures, enamel erosion, and increased sensitivity. This can lead to dental problems, such as cavities, gum disease, and tooth loss.\n\nSecond, eating ice can also cause digestive problems. Consuming large amounts of ice can lead to constipation, as it can reduce the amount of water in your stool and make it harder to pass. It can also cause bloating and abdominal pain.\n\nFinally, eating ice can be a sign of an underlying medical condition, such as anemia or iron deficiency. If you are concerned about your ice-eating habits or have other symptoms, it is important to speak with a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and treatment.\n\nIn summary, while eating a small amount of ice occasionally is not likely to cause significant harm, consuming large amounts of ice regularly can be harmful to your health and may be a sign of an underlying medical condition. It is important to speak with a healthcare professional if you are concerned about your ice-eating habits."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hi,You should see a Dermatologist for proper advice on what treatment to be started.It could very well be an insect bite and I usually prescribe Tab Fexofenadine 120mg twice daily for 5 to 7 days along with some ointment to soothe the itching. But an examination by the Dermatologist would be best.Take care,Dr Rishi, New Delhi, India."}, {"label": 1, "content": "Itchy genital areas can be caused by a variety of factors, including infections, allergies, and skin conditions. It is important to see a healthcare provider to determine the cause and get proper treatment. In the meantime, you can try the following measures to help reduce the itching:\n\nKeep the area clean and dry: Gently wash the area with warm water and mild soap, and make sure to dry thoroughly after showering or bathing.\n\nAvoid irritation: Avoid using perfumed soaps, lotions, or other products on the genital area, as they can cause irritation. Wear loose, breathable clothing to help keep the area dry.\n\nTry over-the-counter creams: There are several over-the-counter creams that can help reduce itching, such as hydrocortisone cream. Follow the instructions on the package for proper use.\n\nTake an antihistamine: If the itching is due to an allergy, an antihistamine such as Benadryl (diphenhydramine) may help reduce the symptoms. Follow the instructions on the package for proper use.\n\nIt is important to see a healthcare provider if the itching persists or if you have any other symptoms, such as discharge or pain. The provider can examine the area and determine the cause of the itching and provide appropriate treatment."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hi, I had gone through your question and understand your concerns.Chronic liver problem will not show up on a colonoscopy report.You could be having fatty liver or hepatitis .It would have been great had I examined you on my own.Do not worry.I would suggest you to - Avoid oily , spicy food- Stop smoking, stop alcohol- Have a healthy diet with loads of vegetables and fruits- Continue the medications- Get a blood liver function test doneVisit a gastroenterologist. He/she can examine you and correlate clinically.Hope this answers your question. If you have additional questions or follow up questions then please do not hesitate in writing to us. I will be happy to answer your questions. Wishing you good health."}, {"label": 1, "content": "I'm sorry to hear that you are experiencing chronic liver problems and other gastrointestinal issues. It is important to follow the treatment plan recommended by your doctor, which in your case includes the use of Motinorm-Dt 10 and Nexito Plus tablets. However, if you are not seeing improvements in your symptoms, it may be helpful to discuss this with your doctor and consider other options for treatment.\n\nIn addition to following your prescribed treatment plan, there are also a few lifestyle changes that you can make to help manage your chronic liver problems and improve your overall health. These include:\n\nEating a healthy diet: A healthy diet that is low in fat, sugar, and salt can help to improve liver function and reduce the risk of liver damage.\n\nExercising regularly: Regular exercise can help to improve your overall health and may also help to improve liver function.\n\nAvoiding alcohol: Alcohol can damage the liver, so it is important to avoid it or to limit your consumption if you do drink.\n\nQuitting smoking: Smoking can also damage the liver, so it is important to quit if you smoke.\n\nReducing stress: Chronic stress can negatively impact your overall health and may also contribute to liver problems. Finding healthy ways to manage stress, such as through exercise, meditation, or therapy, can be beneficial.\n\nIt is also important to continue to follow up with your doctor and to seek medical attention if your symptoms worsen or if you experience any new symptoms. Your doctor may need to adjust your treatment plan or order additional tests to determine the cause of your chronic liver problems and develop a more effective treatment plan."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hi. You have not mentioned the reason for which hysterectomy was done. Before giving a comment, the location of mass should be known. Usually, calretinin stain applied to differentiate between mesothelioma and other metastatic carcinoma or adenocarcinomas. Calretinin can be positive in breast malignancy. Certain ovarian tumor, adrenal cortical tumor, olfactory neuroblastoma, etc., also give positive calretinin reaction. So, mention where the tumor or mass located and accordingly further comment can be given. And histopathology examination is advised for reaching the final diagnosis. Take care. for further information consult a pathologist online --> https://www.icliniq.com/ask-a-doctor-online/pathologist"}, {"label": 1, "content": "beyonddcdcdcdc@163.com\nQ. Kindly explain whether my cytology report shows metastatic breast cancer cells.Hi doctor,I had my cytology report from pelvic wash before hysterectomy. I need some clarifications on the pathology report. The report showed atypical cells - reactive mesothelial cells, enlarged and crowded nuclei, positive for calretinin and negative for Ber-EP4. Could these be metastatic breast cancer cells? I have a previous history of TNBC.\nIt is not possible for me to accurately interpret your cytology report without more information or access to the complete medical record. A cytology report is a laboratory test that involves examining cells under a microscope to look for abnormalities. In this case, the report indicates that atypical cells were found in the sample, and these cells were identified as reactive mesothelial cells based on certain characteristics such as the presence of calretinin and the absence of Ber-EP4.\n\nReactive mesothelial cells are a type of cell that lines the body's internal organs and cavities, including the pelvis. These cells can become enlarged and crowded under certain circumstances, such as inflammation or injury. The presence of reactive mesothelial cells in a cytology sample does not necessarily indicate the presence of cancer.\n\nIf you have a history of breast cancer, it is possible that cancer cells could have spread (metastasized) to other parts of your body, including the pelvis. However, it is not possible to determine whether the atypical cells in your cytology report are metastatic breast cancer cells based on the information provided. It is important to discuss the findings of your cytology report with your doctor and to undergo further testing if necessary to accurately diagnose and treat any underlying medical conditions."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hello and Welcome to \u2018Ask A Doctor\u2019 service. I have reviewed your query and here is my advice. Ferritin levels that are too high can indicate certain conditions. One example is hemochromatosis, which is when your body absorbs too much iron. Hope I have answered your query. Let me know if I can assist you further."}, {"label": 1, "content": "Ferritin is a protein that stores iron in your body. High ferritin levels, also known as hyperferritinemia, can indicate that there is excess iron in the body. This can be due to several factors, including iron overload (also known as hemochromatosis), certain types of anemia, or chronic inflammation.\n\nIt is unusual for ferritin levels to increase significantly within a short period of time, such as a month. It is possible that your mother's ferritin levels were elevated due to an underlying condition that was not previously diagnosed. It is important for her to speak with a healthcare professional to determine the cause of the high ferritin levels and to determine the appropriate course of treatment.\n\nIt is also worth noting that ferritin levels can be affected by other factors, such as recent blood transfusions, liver disease, and certain medications. It is important to consider these factors and discuss them with a healthcare professional as well."}, {"label": 0, "content": "the most common reason for toes to be deformed at a young age is a tendon imbalance between the flexors and extensors of the foot. for example, having a high arch or a cavus type foot, leads to the extensor tendons bowstringing and hammertoe formation. Using a custom orthotic from a foot and ankle specialist may help balance deforming forces. others have advocated taping the toes in an improved position but I never tape children's toes as it potentially can strangulate the toes and cause gangrene. with a certain type of flatfoot, the fourth and fifth toes turn inward due to imbalance of intrinsic tendons of the foot. although these may be cosmetically unappealing I would never consider surgery until all growth plates close after around 18 years of age, and usually don't ever cause negative symptoms"}, {"label": 1, "content": "Overlapping toes, also known as crossed toes or clinodactyly, is a common birth defect that affects the shape of the toes and can cause discomfort or difficulty with walking. In children, the condition is often caused by a lack of space in the womb, which can result in the toes becoming bent and overlapping. Treatment options for overlapping toes in children may include:\n\nSplinting: Using a splint or special shoe inserts can help straighten the toes and improve the alignment of the foot.\n\nStretching exercises: Stretching exercises can help improve the flexibility and range of motion in the toes.\n\nOrthotic devices: Custom-made orthotic devices, such as insoles or arch supports, can help realign the foot and improve the alignment of the toes.\n\nMassage: Massaging the toes and feet can help improve circulation and reduce stiffness in the toes.\n\nSurgery: In severe cases, surgery may be necessary to correct the deformity. However, surgery is generally reserved for cases where other treatment options have not been successful or if the deformity is causing significant discomfort or difficulty with walking.\n\nIt's important to note that treatment for overlapping toes in children may vary depending on the severity of the deformity and the age of the child. It's best to consult with a healthcare professional, such as a pediatrician or a podiatrist, to determine the best course of treatment for your child."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hi,As you said, you brother suffers from psoriasis. It is a chronic and relapsing skin disease. I can understand your anxiety for his disease. But,both of you have to keep patience. He might get relief slowly. And due to some factors it might relapse...Remember it is a controllable disease. And there is no perfect treatment in ayurvedic or homeopathy.You take him to consult nearby dermatologist for firm diagnosis and perfect treatment.I would like to suggest few things as follow....- acitretin 25 mg daily- methotraxate 15 mg weekly in three devided doses of 5 mg 12 hourly.- Blood tests ..routine & LFT may be done at regular intervals- Steroid with salicylic acid oint may be applied twice a day on the psoriatic lesions...on trunk and extremities- But, please avoid the use of betnovate on psoriatic lesions on foreskin and soft tissue areas..as it is a moderately strong steroid....apply mild steroid cream like mometasone.- Soap bath should be avoided.- All precautions may be taken to avoid dryness of skin. Winter might worsen due to dry weather. So, take care.After few months treatment..he may be alright. But, maintenance therapy may be continued. And if there is relapse, he may restart the treatment.Have patience...Dr. Ilyas Patel MD"}, {"label": 1, "content": "There is no cure for psoriasis, but it can be managed with treatment. The goals of treatment are to slow the growth of skin cells, reduce inflammation, and alleviate symptoms such as itching, redness, and scaling. Treatment options for psoriasis include topical medications, light therapy, and oral or injectable medications. The specific treatment plan will depend on the type and severity of the psoriasis, as well as the individual's preference and overall health.\n\nTopical medications, which are applied to the skin, include corticosteroids, vitamin D analogues, and topical retinoids. These medications can help to reduce inflammation and slow the growth of skin cells. Light therapy, also known as phototherapy, involves exposing the skin to controlled amounts of natural or artificial light. This can help to reduce inflammation and slow the growth of skin cells.\n\nOral or injectable medications, also known as systemic therapies, are taken by mouth or injected into the body. These include medications such as methotrexate, cyclosporine, and biologics. Biologics are a newer type of medication that targets specific parts of the immune system. These medications can be effective, but they can also have serious side effects, so they are usually reserved for more severe cases of psoriasis or when other treatments have not been successful.\n\nIt is important to work closely with a dermatologist or other healthcare provider to determine the best treatment plan for you or your loved one. It may take some time to find the right combination of treatments that effectively manage the psoriasis, but with proper treatment, it is possible to reduce the severity of symptoms and improve quality of life."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Dear thanks for the query.Normally kidneys secrete albumin in very small quantity or nothing at all.When your kidney cannot retain protein you should look for the damage to kidney.Please visit a physician or nephrologist and get proper investigation and treatment accordingly.You made ultrasound and other kidney function tests.bye and take care."}, {"label": 1, "content": "High levels of albumin in the urine, also known as albuminuria, can be a sign of kidney damage or a kidney disease such as nephrotic syndrome. It is important to speak with a healthcare provider to determine the cause of the high albumin levels and determine the appropriate course of treatment.\n\nTreatment for albuminuria may involve managing the underlying cause, such as controlling high blood pressure or diabetes, which can help to reduce the damage to the kidneys. Your healthcare provider may also prescribe medications to help reduce protein loss in the urine and protect the kidneys. In some cases, lifestyle changes such as a change in diet or exercise may also be recommended to help manage the condition.\n\nIt is important to follow your healthcare provider's recommendations and to regularly monitor your albumin levels and overall kidney function to ensure that the condition is being properly managed."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hello.Thank you for asking at HCM.I went through your history and would like to make suggestions for you as follows:1. I would suggest you to take an antihistamine like hydroxyzine for 2-3 days. It will help.2. I would also suggest you to avoid hot/spicy foods for a week if it is possible.Hope above suggestions will be helpful to you.Should you have any further query, please feel free to ask at HCM.Wish you the best of the health.Thank you & Regards."}, {"label": 1, "content": "Flushing, or the sensation of warmth and redness in the face and lips, can have many different causes. Some common causes include:\n\nAlcohol or caffeine consumption: These substances can cause blood vessels to dilate, leading to flushing.\n\nSpicy foods: Spicy foods can also cause blood vessels to dilate, leading to flushing.\n\nMenopause: Flushing is a common symptom of menopause, when estrogen levels drop.\n\nRosacea: This is a skin condition that causes rednes