hrough skin tests or blood tests.\n\nImmunotherapy, also known as allergy shots, is another treatment option that can help reduce the severity of allergies over time. This treatment involves receiving a series of injections that contain small amounts of the substances that trigger your allergies. These injections help your body become less sensitive to the allergens over time, leading to a reduction in symptoms.\n\nIt is important to work with a healthcare provider to determine the best treatment options for your specific allergies. They can help you develop a treatment plan that is tailored to your needs and can provide ongoing support and guidance to help you manage your allergies effectively."}, {"label": 0, "content": "Hi Hope this message finds u in good health.I have gone through ur msg and understand your concern.it may be due to some sort of hormonal imbalances or variations in the body,though there may be other reasons as wellNothing to worry about, You should eventually get back to normal.Take multi vitamin and calcium supplements Do consult a gynecologist if symptoms worsenGet back to me for any  FOLLOW UP QUERIES anytime.Regards,Dr Mahaveer Patil...(MBBS,MS,Mch)"}, {"label": 1, "content": "I'm sorry to hear that you are experiencing leg cramps after having your Mirena coil removed. Leg cramps can be caused by various factors, such as muscle fatigue, dehydration, certain medications, and hormonal imbalances. It is possible that the removal of the Mirena coil could have caused a hormonal imbalance, which could be contributing to the leg cramps you are experiencing. However, it is important to note that every person is different, and it is possible that your leg cramps could be caused by something else. It is always a good idea to speak with a healthcare professional if you are experiencing persistent or severe leg cramps, as they can help determine the cause and provide appropriate treatment. I hope this information is helpful."}, {"label": 0, "content": "